                "position": {
                  "x": 160,
                  "y": 210
                },
                "font_size": 12
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "formula_box",
            "equation": "Smooth surface: F = N   (because f = 0)",
            "position": {
              "x": 380,
              "y": 430
            }
          }
        ],
        "teacher_script": {
          "tts_sentences": [
            {
              "id": "s1",
              "text_en": "A smooth surface means friction is zero. No sliding resistance at all."
            },
            {
              "id": "s2",
              "text_en": "So the total contact force F equals the square root of N squared plus zero, which is simply N itself."
            },
            {
              "id": "s3",
              "text_en": "On smooth problems, the contact force is just the normal reaction. The friction piece vanishes."
            },
            {
              "id": "s4",
              "text_en": "Remember this for exams: the word smooth is a promise that f equals zero."
            }
          ]
        },
        "advance_mode": "auto_after_tts"
      },
      "STATE_6": {
